    <section class="tvm-local-intro">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="tvm-local-grid">
          <div class="tvm-local-copy">
            <div class="section-eyebrow" style="color:var(--tvm-accent)">Serving Culver City</div>
            <h2 class="section-heading" style="margin:0 0 20px">Old city, new builds.<br />Every wall handled.</h2>
            <p>Culver City has undergone significant new construction in the last decade — converted warehouse lofts, new condo towers, and mixed-use buildings along Washington and Sepulveda sit alongside original 1940s wood-frame bungalows in the older residential neighborhoods. The older and newer construction require completely different mounting approaches: wood studs at standard spacing in the bungalows, and steel-stud or concrete in the newer builds.</p>
            <p>Our installers have worked across Culver City’s varied housing — in the Hayden Tract lofts, the newer residential developments near Platform, and the established single-family neighborhoods around Carlson Park. They’re familiar with the city’s mix of pre-war construction, mid-century homes, and recent high-density residential.</p>
            <p>We serve all of Culver City and the surrounding areas. Whether you’re in a converted production studio loft or a 1950s ranch home, the approach is the same: assess the wall, verify the structure, mount correctly, and leave nothing visible but the screen.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tvm-local-areas">
            <div class="section-eyebrow" style="color:var(--tvm-accent);margin-bottom:16px">Neighborhoods We Serve</div>
            <div class="tvm-areas-grid">
              <span class="tvm-area-pill">Downtown Culver City</span>
              <span class="tvm-area-pill">Carlson Park</span>
              <span class="tvm-area-pill">Hayden Tract</span>
              <span class="tvm-area-pill">Fox Hills</span>
              <span class="tvm-area-pill">Blair Hills</span>
              <span class="tvm-area-pill">Culver Crest</span>
              <span class="tvm-area-pill">Sunkist Park</span>
              <span class="tvm-area-pill">Mar Vista</span>
              <span class="tvm-area-pill">Palms</span>
              <span class="tvm-area-pill">Venice</span>
              <span class="tvm-area-pill">Marina del Rey</span>
              <span class="tvm-area-pill">Westside</span>
              <span class="tvm-area-pill">Baldwin Hills</span>
              <span class="tvm-area-pill">Jefferson Park</span>
              <span class="tvm-area-pill">Ladera Heights</span>
            
            </div>
            <p class="tvm-areas-note">Don’t see your neighborhood? Call us — we serve all of Culver City and surrounding areas.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider--cream"></div>

    <section class="pain-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="pain-intro fade-up visible">
          <div class="section-eyebrow" style="color:#dc2626">Why Most TV Mounts Fail</div>
          <h2 class="section-heading">A crooked TV. Wires everywhere.<br /><em style="color:#dc2626">A wall you can't undo.</em></h2>
          <p class="section-body">TV mounting looks straightforward until it isn't. The wrong stud, the wrong anchor, or a bracket that's slightly off-level — and suddenly you're living with a $1,200 decision you regret every time you sit on the couch.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pain-grid">
          <div class="pain-card fade-up"><div class="pain-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linejoin="round"></path><path d="M9 12l2 2 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></div><h3>Mounted into drywall, not a stud</h3><p>The most common DIY mistake — and the most expensive. Drywall anchors rated for 50 lbs holding a 90-lb TV over the couch is not a risk worth taking. A mount that misses the stud pulls out slowly over weeks of thermal expansion and vibration. We locate and verify studs with both a finder and a physical tap before a single screw goes in.</p></div>
          <div class="pain-card fade-up d1"><div class="pain-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M4 19.5A2.5 2.5 0 016.5 17H20" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path><path d="M6.5 2H20v20H6.5A2.5 2.5 0 014 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 016.5 2z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></path><path d="M12 8v8M8 12h8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div><h3>Cables draped down the wall</h3><p>A beautifully mounted TV with three cords hanging to the floor defeats the entire purpose. It looks unfinished and signals immediately that the install wasn't professional. Proper wire management means routing cables through the wall or a surface raceway that's painted to match — completely invisible when we leave.</p></div>
          <div class="pain-card fade-up d2"><div class="pain-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></circle><path d="M12 8v4l3 3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></div><h3>Off-level by just a few degrees</h3><p>Two degrees off-level sounds negligible. You notice it every single time you look at the screen. And once it's in the wall, correcting it means filling the original holes, waiting for them to cure, sanding, spot-painting, and starting over. We verify level with a digital tool before final tightening.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="agitate-block fade-up d1 visible">
          <div class="agitate-text">
            <h2>The install was fine. <em>Until it wasn't.</em></h2>
            <p>A failed mount rarely fails immediately. The bracket holds for three months — then one anchor works loose, the TV tilts, and you're repairing a wall hoping the screen survived. We've remounted hundreds of TVs installed by homeowners and unqualified handymen. The pattern never changes: wrong hardware, wrong placement, no stud check.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="agitate-stats">
            <div class="agitate-stat fade-up d2 visible"><div class="as-num">62%</div><div><div class="as-text-label">of DIY TV mounts miss at least one stud</div><div class="as-text-sub">Based on our technicians' re-mount assessments</div></div></div>
            <div class="agitate-stat fade-up d3 visible"><div class="as-num">$340</div><div><div class="as-text-label">average cost to repair a failed self-install</div><div class="as-text-sub">Wall repair + repaint + re-mount adds up fast</div></div></div>
            <div class="agitate-stat fade-up d4 visible"><div class="as-num">2°</div><div><div class="as-text-label">is all it takes to notice a TV is off-level</div><div class="as-text-sub">The human eye detects tilts as small as 1–2 degrees</div></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <section class="solve-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="solve-grid">
          <div class="solve-photo-col fade-up">
            <img class="solve-photo" src="/images/tv-mounting-solve.png" alt="TV professionally mounted in modern living room" loading="lazy" width="800" height="520" />
            <div class="solve-badge"><div class="solve-badge-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M10 2l2 5h5l-4 3 1.5 5L10 12 5.5 15 7 10 3 7h5L10 2Z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg></div><div><div class="solve-badge-num">4.8★</div><div class="solve-badge-label">TV mounting avg. rating</div></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="solve-copy fade-up d1 visible">
            <div class="section-eyebrow">The Standard We Hold</div>
            <h2 class="solve-heading">Clean. Level. <em>Permanent.</em></h2>
            <p>We don't eyeball level. We don't guess at studs. Every install starts with a stud finder and a physical tap to confirm placement. The bracket goes into solid wood or the correct masonry anchor — never drywall alone. Cables are routed through the wall or a painted raceway so the only thing you see is the screen.</p>
            <p>We use the right mount for your wall type and TV weight. Full-motion arms get structural verification; fireplace installs get masonry-rated hardware. When we leave, the TV is level, secure, and built to stay that way.</p>
            <div class="solve-points">
              <div class="solve-point"><div class="sp-icon"><svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none"><path d="M2 7l3 3 7-7" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></div><div class="sp-text"><strong>Stud-verified before every screw.</strong> <span>Finder plus physical verification — no guesswork.</span></div></div>
              <div class="solve-point"><div class="sp-icon"><svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none"><path d="M2 7l3 3 7-7" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></div><div class="sp-text"><strong>Wire concealment included.</strong> <span>Through the wall or surface raceway — your choice, clean result.</span></div></div>
              <div class="solve-point"><div class="sp-icon"><svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none"><path d="M2 7l3 3 7-7" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></div><div class="sp-text"><strong>Digital level, not eyeballed.</strong> <span>Verified before we tighten — no tilt, no regrets.</span></div></div>
              <div class="solve-point"><div class="sp-icon"><svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none"><path d="M2 7l3 3 7-7" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></div><div class="sp-text"><strong>Right bracket for your wall type.</strong> <span>Drywall, plaster, brick, stone — we bring the correct hardware.</span></div></div>
            </div>
            <button type="button" class="btn-primary-gold tvm-book-btn" data-open-booking="true" data-service="TV Mounting"><svg width="17" height="17" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M10 2l2 5h5l-4 3 1.5 5L10 12 5.5 15 7 10 3 7h5L10 2Z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg> Book a TV Mounting</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <section class="services-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="services-intro">
          <div class="section-eyebrow fade-up">What We Offer</div>
          <h2 class="section-heading fade-up d1">Every type of mount. Every type of wall.</h2>
          <p class="section-body fade-up d2" style="margin:0 auto;">From fixed and tilting mounts to full-motion arms, in-wall wire concealment, and above-fireplace installs — we handle it all with the right hardware and certified installers who do this every day.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="services-grid">
          <div class="svc-card fade-up visible"><div class="svc-card-top"><div class="svc-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><rect x="2" y="4" width="20" height="14" rx="2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></rect><path d="M8 22h8M12 18v4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div><h3>Fixed &amp; Tilting Mounts</h3></div><p>Low-profile fixed or tilt-adjustable brackets for any TV up to 100"+, stud-verified and torqued to spec.</p><a class="svc-card-link" href="#" data-open-quote="true" data-service="TV Mounting">Get a quote <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M2 6h8M6 2l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></a></div>
          <div class="svc-card fade-up d1 visible"><div class="svc-card-top"><div class="svc-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M4 12h16M12 4v16" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div><h3>Full-Motion Articulating Arms</h3></div><p>Extends, swivels, tilts — ideal for corners or multi-seating rooms. Mounted into sufficient structure to handle extended leverage.</p><a class="svc-card-link" href="#" data-open-quote="true" data-service="TV Mounting">Get a quote <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M2 6h8M6 2l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></a></div>
          <div class="svc-card fade-up d2 visible"><div class="svc-card-top"><div class="svc-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 2v4M12 18v4M4 12h4M16 12h4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div><h3>In-Wall Wire Concealment</h3></div><p>Cut access plates, fish cables through wall cavity, install low-voltage wall plates. Code-compliant, completely clean result.</p><a class="svc-card-link" href="#" data-open-quote="true" data-service="TV Mounting">Get a quote <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M2 6h8M6 2l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></a></div>
          <div class="svc-card fade-up d3 visible"><div class="svc-card-top"><div class="svc-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M4 22h16M8 22V12h8v10M4 12l8-8 8 8M12 4v4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></div><h3>Above Fireplace Install</h3></div><p>Stone, brick, tile surrounds need masonry anchors and a steeper tilt. We've completed hundreds across LA and bring the right hardware for every surround material.</p><a class="svc-card-link" href="#" data-open-quote="true" data-service="TV Mounting">Get a quote <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M2 6h8M6 2l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></a></div>
          <div class="svc-card fade-up visible"><div class="svc-card-top"><div class="svc-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M3 18h18M3 14h18M3 10h6M12 10h9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div><h3>Soundbar &amp; Speaker Mounting</h3></div><p>Soundbar flush under the TV, audio cable through the wall, surround speakers at correct angle and height for your room.</p><a class="svc-card-link" href="#" data-open-quote="true" data-service="TV Mounting">Get a quote <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M2 6h8M6 2l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></a></div>
          <div class="svc-card fade-up d1 visible"><div class="svc-card-top"><div class="svc-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><rect x="2" y="4" width="8" height="14" rx="1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></rect><rect x="14" y="4" width="8" height="14" rx="1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></rect></svg></div><h3>Dual &amp; Multi-Monitor Setup</h3></div><p>Home office arms, trading setups, commercial displays. Precise alignment, cable management for multiple feeds, structural mounting for combined weight.</p><a class="svc-card-link" href="#" data-open-quote="true" data-service="TV Mounting">Get a quote <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M2 6h8M6 2l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></a></div>
          <div class="svc-card fade-up d2 visible"><div class="svc-card-top"><div class="svc-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></circle><path d="M12 2v4M12 18v4M4 12h4M16 12h4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div><h3>Outdoor TV Mounting</h3></div><p>Marine-grade mounts, weatherproof conduit or direct-burial cable, every penetration sealed against moisture.</p><a class="svc-card-link" href="#" data-open-quote="true" data-service="TV Mounting">Get a quote <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M2 6h8M6 2l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></a></div>
          <div class="svc-card fade-up d3 visible"><div class="svc-card-top"><div class="svc-card-icon"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M4 19.5A2.5 2.5 0 016.5 17H20" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path><path d="M6.5 2H20v20H6.5A2.5 2.5 0 014 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 016.5 2z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></path></svg></div><h3>Concrete &amp; Brick Wall Installs</h3></div><p>Hammer-drill bits, sleeve anchors, correct torque spec. We carry masonry equipment as standard — not an upsell.</p><a class="svc-card-link" href="#" data-open-quote="true" data-service="TV Mounting">Get a quote <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M2 6h8M6 2l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></a></div>
