    <section class="faq-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="faq-intro">
          <div class="section-eyebrow fade-up">FAQ</div>
          <h2 class="section-heading fade-up d1">Every question before booking, answered.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-cols fade-up d1 visible">
          <div class="faq-col">
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" class="faq-q"><span class="faq-question-text">How much does TV mounting cost?</span><div class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>A straightforward TV mount — no wire concealment, no add-ons — starts at $95 for TVs under 50" and $160 for larger sets. That's the floor for a clean, stud-verified install with the correct hardware included. Most customers add in-wall wire concealment or a soundbar mount, which changes the price — but every add-on is quoted separately and upfront before we touch anything. You'll know the full number before the job starts.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" class="faq-q"><span class="faq-question-text">Do I need to buy a mount first?</span><div class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>No. We supply the mount as part of the job unless you already have one you want to use. We use commercial-grade brackets rated for your TV's weight and VESA pattern. If you have an existing mount, we can install it provided it's appropriate for the application — we'll confirm during the quote.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" class="faq-q"><span class="faq-question-text">Can you hide the wires in the wall?</span><div class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. In-wall wire concealment is included in our standard TV mounting service where structure allows. We cut access plates, fish HDMI and power (or use a power kit where code requires), and install low-voltage wall plates. The result is a clean wall with no visible cables. If full in-wall isn't possible, we use a surface raceway painted to match.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" class="faq-q"><span class="faq-question-text">What if there are no studs where I want the TV?</span><div class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>We always prefer to hit at least one stud; for larger TVs we use two. If the ideal viewing spot falls between studs, we have options: a mount that spans to the nearest studs, or for certain walls we can use heavy-duty toggle anchors rated for the load when studs aren't available. We'll assess on site and never install into drywall alone for a heavy TV.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" class="faq-q"><span class="faq-question-text">How long does a TV mounting take?</span><div class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Most single-TV installs with wire concealment take 1–2 hours from start to cleanup. Full-motion mounts or above-fireplace installs can run a bit longer. We'll give you a window when we confirm the appointment; we arrive with all tools and hardware so there's no second trip.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" class="faq-q"><span class="faq-question-text">Can you mount a TV above a fireplace?</span><div class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. We've done hundreds of above-fireplace installs on stone, brick, tile, and drywall surrounds. We use masonry anchors and the correct drill bits; we also typically use a tilting mount to improve viewing angle. Heat isn't usually an issue with modern TVs when the mantel provides separation, but we can discuss your specific setup.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" class="faq-q"><span class="faq-question-text">Do you work in Culver City’s converted lofts and new construction buildings?</span><div class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes — we work in Culver City’s newer construction regularly, including the converted industrial lofts in the Hayden Tract and the newer residential buildings near Downtown. Concrete walls and steel-stud construction are a standard part of our work. We carry masonry hardware and sleeve anchors as default equipment — not an upsell you have to request.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-col">
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" class="faq-q"><span class="faq-question-text">Do you bring all the tools and hardware?</span><div class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Our installers arrive with every tool needed: stud finders, levels, drills, bits, anchors, mounts, and cable management supplies. You don't need to provide anything except the TV and a clear area. We'll confirm mount choice and any add-ons (e.g. soundbar bracket) before the visit.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" class="faq-q"><span class="faq-question-text">What TV sizes do you mount?</span><div class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>We mount everything from small displays (32" and up) to large formats (85", 90", 100" and beyond). The mount and hardware are sized to your TV's weight and VESA pattern. For very large or heavy TVs we use two-person handling and appropriate brackets — just tell us the size when you request a quote.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" class="faq-q"><span class="faq-question-text">Can you fix a mount someone else installed?</span><div class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. We often remount TVs that were installed incorrectly — wrong stud placement, off-level, or failing hardware. We can unmount, patch holes if needed, and reinstall with stud verification and a clean finish. You get a fresh quote for the re-mount and any wall repair.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" class="faq-q"><span class="faq-question-text">Do you work in apartments?</span><div class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. We work in apartments and condos regularly. In-wall wire concealment may be limited by building rules or construction (e.g. fire blocks); we can use surface raceways where in-wall isn't allowed. We're insured and professional; building management is usually fine when we're hired by the tenant.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" class="faq-q"><span class="faq-question-text">Is your work guaranteed?</span><div class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Every install is covered by our 90-day workmanship guarantee. If anything shifts, loosens, or isn't level within 90 days, we come back and fix it at no charge. One call — no forms or runaround. We also stand behind the quote: the price we give you is the price you pay.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" class="faq-q"><span class="faq-question-text">How do I book?</span><div class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Fill out the quote form on this page or call (818) 584-7389. We respond within an hour with a firm price and availability. Same-day slots are often available when you book before noon. Once you confirm, we'll send your installer's name and arrival window.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" class="faq-q"><span class="faq-question-text">My Culver City home is a 1940s bungalow — will stud finding be difficult?</span><div class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Older wood-frame bungalows in Culver City have standard 16"-on-center stud layouts that are generally predictable. What can complicate things is the plaster-over-lath finish common in pre-1950 construction — standard stud finders don’t always read through it cleanly. We use both electronic and physical verification methods and have located studs in hundreds of Culver City bungalows without issue.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

